				<td colspan="2"><span>a couple suggestions:
<br />

<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=23616">Spaulders of the Slavemaster</a>
<br />

<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=17885">Composer's Boots</a> - never sell your SS boots as they are useful for the clicky forever.  Ornate boots are kind of a must have for a bard about to get FM.  There are nicer boots in terms of stats but the FT3 on them is nice.
<br />

<br />
Get a few levels on you and see if you can get a group in the first field in WoS.  You may get lucky and pick up a <a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=30482">Bloodstone of the Dance</a>
<br />

<br />
Apart from that, the Magnetic armor is very nice.  The Charged is way expensive because of what the charging components are going for and not that much stellar in terms of stats.  But something like the <a target="_new" href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=30733">Magnetic Helm</a> would be a serious long term upgrade for not a huge investment.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
